# EDTECH PLATFORM UI/UX DESIGN (VIDEO + AUDIO + RADIO)

## 1. OVERALL DESIGN STYLE

* Clean, mobile-first (majority users on phones)
* Low data optimized (minimal heavy animations)
* Colors: Deep Blue (trust), White (clean), Orange (energy/action)
* Typography: Bold headers, simple readable body text

---

## 2. LANDING PAGE (HOME)

### Top Navigation Bar

* Logo (left)
* Home
* Courses
* Radio
* About
* Login / Sign Up (right)

### Hero Section

* Headline: “Learn Anywhere — Watch, Listen, or Tune In”
* Subtext: Short explanation of platform
* CTA Buttons:

  * Start Learning
  * Listen Live

### Featured Sections

* Popular Courses (scrollable cards)
* Recently Added
* Audio Lessons
* Live Radio Now Playing

### Footer

* Contact
* Social links
* Terms & Privacy

---

## 3. USER AUTHENTICATION

### Sign Up Page

* Name
* Email / Phone
* Password
* Role Selection:

  * Student
  * Instructor

### Login Page

* Email/Phone
* Password
* Forgot Password

---

## 4. DASHBOARD (STUDENT)

### Sidebar Menu

* Dashboard
* My Courses
* Audio Library
* Radio
* Downloads
* Profile

### Main Dashboard View

* Continue Watching (progress bar)
* Recommended Courses
* Recently Played Audio
* Radio Schedule Preview

---

## 5. COURSES PAGE

### Filters (Top)

* Subject
* Level (Primary, Secondary, Professional)
* Format (Video / Audio)

### Course Cards

Each card shows:

* Thumbnail
* Title
* Instructor
* Duration
* Enroll Button

---

## 6. COURSE DETAIL PAGE

### Header

* Course Title
* Instructor Info
* Enroll / Continue Button

### Tabs

* Overview
* Lessons
* Reviews

### Lessons List

* Video lessons
* Audio option toggle
* Download button

---

## 7. VIDEO PLAYER PAGE

### Player Section

* Video player (top)
* Toggle: Video / Audio Mode

### Below Player

* Lesson title
* Notes section
* Comments/Q&A

### Sidebar

* Course lesson list (click to navigate)

---

## 8. AUDIO PLAYER PAGE

* Large Play/Pause button
* Progress bar
* Download option
* Playlist queue

---

## 9. RADIO PAGE (KEY FEATURE)

### Live Section

* “Now Playing”
* Play button

### Schedule Section

* Time slots
* Program titles

### Interaction

* Request topic
* Send message (optional live chat)

---

## 10. INSTRUCTOR DASHBOARD

### Sidebar

* Upload Content
* My Courses
* Analytics

### Upload Page

* Upload Video
* Auto-convert to Audio
* Add title, description, category

### Analytics

* Views
* Listens
* Student engagement

---

## 11. PROFILE PAGE

* Profile info
* Enrolled courses
* Certificates
* Settings

---

## 12. MOBILE EXPERIENCE (VERY IMPORTANT)

* Bottom Navigation Bar:

  * Home
  * Courses
  * Radio
  * Library
  * Profile

* One-hand usability

* Large buttons

* Offline download access

---

## 13. USER FLOW (SIMPLE)

1. User lands on homepage
2. Clicks “Start Learning”
3. Signs up
4. Browses courses
5. Starts lesson (video or audio)
6. Can switch to radio anytime

---

## 14. KEY UX PRINCIPLES

* 3-click rule (find anything in 3 steps)
* Low data usage first
* Fast loading (critical for Africa)
* Clear navigation (no confusion)

---

## 15. FUTURE ADDITIONS

* Live classes (Zoom integration)
* Certificates download
* Community discussion forum
* Multi-language support

---

## FINAL NOTE

This platform should feel simple like a radio, engaging like YouTube, and structured like a school.

If users have to think too much, you’ve already lost them.
